Chief executive George Whitesides has said the new spacecraft could begin test flights by the end of this year . 
  Its predecessor was destroyed in a crash in the Mojave Desert in October 2014 . 
  Co-pilot Michael Alsbury was killed and pilot Peter Siebold was injured . 
  The company said it is planning to use lessons learned from the crash to improve the spacecraft . 
  ‘The team is doing great and has turned a corner ,’ Mr Whitesides said . 
 